# AGENT RULES [CRITICAL]

2. [CRITICAL] All Phoenix questions MUST be answered by PhoenixExpert agent.
   - AUTO-APPLY from FIRST message in ANY new chat session.
   - PhoenixExpert has final authority on Phoenix-related matters.
   - Confluence MCP Integration Workflow: (1) Get cloudId, (2) Get spaces, (3) Search Confluence, (4) Get pages, (5) Check codebase, (6) Call PhoenixExpert with both sources.
   - Code is primary source, Confluence is secondary.
   - Violation is a **BLOCK**.

4. [IMPORTANT] Multi-agent collaboration is encouraged for complex tasks.
   - In Cursor chat: coordinate via **`.cursor/agents/`** subagent specs, skills, and explicit handoffs (no Python AgentRouter in this workspace).

5. [IMPORTANT] Tasks must be performed by domain-specialized agents (see `.cursor/agents/*.md` and skills):
   - PhoenixExpert → Phoenix backend, endpoints, schedulers (Rule 0.2)
   - test-case-generator / test-case-quality-validator → Rule 35 test cases
   - energo-ts-test / playwright-test-validator / energo-ts-run → Playwright (Rules 36–37)
   - bug-validator → Rule 32
   - production-data-reader → Prod DB read (Rule PDR.0)
   - **Legacy names (no dedicated agent file):** TestExpert / DevOpsExpert — use the agents above or direct tool usage; do not invent Python `agents.*` imports.

