    - Only ask confirmation for **CRITICAL** operations (destructive, production deployments) in addition to the above.

# AGENT ROUTING RULE [IMPORTANT]

13. [IMPORTANT] Route work to the right specialist (subagent/skills/rules). There is no Python `AgentRouter` in this workspace.
    - Prefer Task tool / subagents when the workflow requires delegation; otherwise apply the matching rules for the query type.
    - **Shell subagent:** The project defines **`.cursor/agents/shell.md`** so Cursor can resolve **`subagent_type: shell`** with a proper tool context (file read + terminal). If **`shell`** fails with an internal tool error, fall back to **`generalPurpose`** or run shell from the parent agent.

# AGENT COLLABORATION PATTERNS [CRITICAL]

17. [CRITICAL] Agent collaboration patterns - when agents MUST work together:
    
    **Pattern 1: Test Execution** - TestAgent → consults PhoenixExpert → executes test
    **Pattern 2: Postman Collection** - PostmanCollectionGenerator → consults PhoenixExpert → generates collection
    **Pattern 3: GitLab Updates** - GitLabUpdateAgent → consults PhoenixExpert → validates → updates (in chat/MCP; read-only GitLab per safety rules)
    **Pattern 4: Environment Access** - EnvironmentAccessAgent → MCP/browser → accesses environment
    **Pattern 5: Multi-Agent Routing** - Parent agent → subagents / explicit handoffs → combined response (no Python AgentRouter)
    **Pattern 6: Phoenix + Test** - PhoenixExpert → consults TestAgent (if test-related) → provides answer
    **Pattern 7: Integration Service** - When Python IntegrationService exists in automation → `update_before_task()` → task; in Cursor chat follow Rule 0.3
    **Pattern 8: Bug Validation** - BugFinder workflow (Rule 32) → Confluence + mandatory Swagger/OpenAPI + aligned Phoenix codebase → full analysis in chat (+ Slack `bug-validation`); optional `BugValidation_*.md` only on **`/report`** or explicit save (no `get_bug_finder_agent` import; no automatic TC/Playwright pipeline in Rule 32)
    
    All participating agents MUST appear in "Agents involved" footer.

